  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.5`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nContinuous syncing\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nSyncing stops at block 6485846\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nThe node stopped suddenly a few hours ago. I restarted it, it resynced the last few hundred blocks and got stuck again at the same block.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\n````\r\n########## BAD BLOCK #########\r\nChain config: {ChainID: 3 Homestead: 0 DAO: <nil> DAOSupport: true EIP150: 0 EIP155: 10 EIP158: 10 Byzantium: 1700000 Constantinople: 4230000 Petersburg: 4939394 Istanbul: 6485846 Engine: ethash}\r\n\r\nNumber: 6485846\r\nHash: 0x5bd02cabf0bedac8168e43e25e0c306d1140139b5f5b02a08b18464dd9b5dc6b\r\n         0: cumulative: 186413 gas: 186413 contract: 0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 status: 1 tx: 0xa18915222e16543aab076d05b5f9ec804906ca1767cf208986e32df67b6ffeaa logs: [0xc017eb5a20] bloom:  state:\r\n\r\n\r\nError: invalid gas used (remote: 162041 local: 186413)\r\n##############################\r\n\r\n````\r\nAdditional info: https://ropsten.etherscan.io/ has stopped, as well. \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/51915615/65870924-9b740580-e37d-11e9-93a5-520ec3730592.png)\r\n",
